INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'c18a8ac2-c77d-45b7-ac39-ec8574587f24',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$PHP Unit Testing — PHPUnit Philosophy and Writing Tests That Actually Catch Bugs$escape$,
  $escape$PHPUnit is PHP's de facto test runner — installed via Composer, configured with `phpunit.xml`. The core philosophy is arrange-act-assert: set up state, invoke behavior, verify outcomes. Each test class extends `PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase` and each test method is prefixed with `test` or annotated with `#[Test]`.

Prefer `assertSame()` over `assertEquals()` — the former enforces strict type equality (`1 !== '1'`), catching PHP's loose comparison traps. Use `expectException()` before the act phase to assert thrown exceptions rather than wrapping in try/catch.

For isolation, PHPUnit's `createMock()` generates test doubles at runtime via reflection. Stub dependencies with `method()->willReturn()` to unit-test a class without hitting the database or HTTP. Use `setUp()` to share fixture construction across tests and `tearDown()` for cleanup.

Pest PHP is a modern alternative built on PHPUnit — it adds a Vitest-style closure API (`it()`, `expect()`, `beforeEach()`) with zero boilerplate. Both runners support parallel execution via `--process-isolation`. Run only the failing suite with `--filter=MethodName` during red-green cycles.$escape$,
  $escape$<?php
use PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase;

class OrderServiceTest extends TestCase
{
    private OrderService $service;

    protected function setUp(): void
    {
        $repo = $this->createMock(OrderRepository::class);
        $repo->method('find')->willReturn(new Order(id: 1, total: 99.99));
        $this->service = new OrderService($repo);
    }

    #[Test]
    public function it_applies_discount_to_order(): void
    {
        $result = $this->service->applyDiscount(orderId: 1, percent: 10);
        $this->assertSame(89.99, $result->total);
    }
}$escape$,
